### FHIR Encounter — VERSION_NEUTRAL, served at /fhir/R4/... (no /v1 prefix).

@fhirBase = http://127.0.0.1:3000/fhir/R4

### Create an Encounter referencing an existing Patient
### (replace SUBJECT_ID with a Patient uuid returned by Patient create)
POST {{fhirBase}}/Encounter
Content-Type: application/fhir+json
Authorization: Bearer {{at_token}}

{
  "resourceType": "Encounter",
  "status": "in-progress",
  "class": { "system": "http://terminology.hl7.org/CodeSystem/v3-ActCode", "code": "IMP", "display": "inpatient encounter" },
  "subject": { "reference": "Patient/SUBJECT_ID" },
  "period": { "start": "2026-06-26T08:00:00Z" }
}

### Read an Encounter by id
GET {{fhirBase}}/Encounter/REPLACE_WITH_ID
Authorization: Bearer {{at_token}}

### Search by subject → searchset Bundle
GET {{fhirBase}}/Encounter?subject=Patient/SUBJECT_ID
Authorization: Bearer {{at_token}}

### Dangling reference → 422 OperationOutcome (service pre-resolution)
POST {{fhirBase}}/Encounter
Content-Type: application/fhir+json
Authorization: Bearer {{at_token}}

{
  "resourceType": "Encounter",
  "status": "planned",
  "class": { "code": "AMB" },
  "subject": { "reference": "Patient/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000" }
}
